              Not particularly. We have free legal advice from the company we effectively outsource our HR management to (we have one HR person / PA to the man at the top).<br />Apparently it's a legal requirement for us to have a Data Protection Officer (who knew?) which was only stipulated by the legal team of our now-owners at the time of buyout.<br />There's certainly no on-site legal personnel.<br />We could get the 'on call' people in and say 'tell us what we need to know for this standard' but, again, this is something that should surely be done by the management of the company, not a Systems Admin?

              

              
              
