              I agree. As far as I'm aware, there was 'some money' left in the pot. Unfortunately, the division that we've been subsumed into made a loss this year, and as a result the entire division has been slapped with a moratorium on spend and new staff. As a new member of such division, even though we had nothing to do with the state of affairs, we too have been hit with that, so any money that there <span style="font-style: italic">was</span>, can no longer be spent.<br /><br />It's all pretty ridiculous, not to mention incredibly dangerous given that we're beyond the limit on stuff like backups.<br />I've now been here six months and achieved a lot for very little (i.e. zero) money, simply using what they already had, but hadn't leveraged. If this is still the case in another six months though, then it's bad times.<br /><br />I'm still psyching myself up for a chat with our boss about this whole thing before we break for Easter (in about an hour).

              

              
              
